
[1]vicinity

   VICIN'ITY, n. [L. vicinitas.]

   1. Nearness in place; as the vicinity of two country seats.

   2. Neighborhood; as a seat in the vicinity of the metropolis.

   3. Neighboring country. Vegetables produced in the vicinity of the
   city, are daily brought to market. the vicinity is full of gardens.
